{
  "texts": [
    "As shown in Figure 7, (C1) is the baseline condition with only FoV restriction but no data fusion for comparison, (C2, C4) implement the magic NeRF lens effect with FoV restriction, and (C3, C5) implement the magic NeRF lens effect with 3D drawing.",
    "(C2, C3) use a polygonal representation of a CAD model with colored abstract texture, while (C4, C5) use a polygonal representation of the CAD model with only edging rendering.",
    "The user study was conducted on the same graphics workstation and software configuration used for the system benchmark described in Section 5.",
    "For all conditions, the FoV of the NeRF rendering camera was set to 30 °with a per-eye render resolution of 1200 × 1200 pixel, which is one of the optimal rendering Frontiers in Virtual Reality frontiersin.org configurations determined in our benchmark experiments.",
    "We used an Oculus Quest Pro VR HMD, which has a PDD value of 22."
  ]
}